  "instructions": [
    "In a large pot, heat sesame oil over medium heat. Add onion and garlic; saut\u00e9 until translucent.",
    "Add diced carrots and potatoes, cook for about 5 minutes. Stir in cornmeal and broth, bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for about 20-30 minutes or until thickened.",
    "Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper. Add broccoli florets towards the end of cooking time if you prefer them slightly crisp.",
    "Serve hot as is or with steamed rice."
